This paper is primarily focused on generating images from text descriptions, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. However, it also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as text embedding and regeneration, which are relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) categories. The paper also utilizes attention mechanisms and generative models, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
